description:
&lt;p&gt;The East Direct Commissioning Primary Care &amp; Public Health Team are responsible for overseeing the commissioning in accordance with local and national commissioning strategies and priorities, of Primary Care Services including; General Practice, Dentistry, Pharmacy, Optometry and Public Health.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;As a Commissioning Support Officer, the post holder will work as a part of a dynamic team in delivering an effective service supporting managers and staff across East of England region to deliver the direct commissioning functions for primary care and public health Section 7A services for the Region. &lt;br /&gt;The post holder will act as a relationship manager with a key role in ensuring that the work of the commissioning support hub is monitored and managed effectively.&lt;br /&gt;The successful candidate will demonstrate experience in effective maintenance of administrative systems, communications and stakeholder management for both internal and external organisations and agencies, problem solving and meeting scheduling. &lt;br /&gt;The post holder is a key member of the Primary Care and Public Health team whose overarching purpose is to manage the administrative support needed to facilitate the wider Direct Commissioning teams within Primary Care and Public Health to carry out its functions.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Please note that the reason for the fixed term of your contract is maternity cover.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Key Job specifics and responsibilities&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Key accountabilities&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;To be responsible for the smooth and effective maintenance of the administrative function and systems of the organisation in conjunction with other administration staff.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;The post holder must work on their own initiative with a sound understanding of the business of the organisation and current practices to manage workload and ensure information is communicated appropriately and enquiries are directed correctly.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;The post holder liaises with a wide range of people, partner organisations and agencies, both internally and externally on behalf of the Director/senior manager, ensuring that a professional image is maintained at all times through appropriate use of language and behaviour&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Responsible for managing complex and sensitive business and communication on behalf of the Primary Care &amp; Public Health Team, solving problems and responding to unexpected demands&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Organising meeting, conferences as requested involving internal colleagues and high level stakeholders.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Improving quality and outcomes&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;· To support in ensuring high quality primary care services are commissioned on behalf of the population served.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Enabling patient and public involvement&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;· To act as a champion for patients and their interests and involve the public and patients in the policy development and decision-making of NHS England.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;· To ensure all public and patient contact with the office is of the highest professional standard.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;· To embed patient and public involvement within NHS England at all levels of decision making.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Promoting equality and reducing inequalities&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;· To uphold organisational policies and principles on the promotion of equality.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;· To create an inclusive working environment where diversity is valued, everyone can contribute, and everyday action and ensure we meet our duty to uphold and promote equality.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Partnership and cross boundary working&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;· To work in partnership with others across the Directorate to deliver successful outcomes.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;· Support colleagues from across the East DCO when required to do so to ensure delivery of the business needs as outlined in the work in the work programme.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;· To develop and maintain close and effective working relationships with key stakeholders and organisations.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Leadership for transformational change&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;· To model a collaborative and influencing style of working, negotiating with others to achieve the best outcomes. Embedding this approach across the Directorate.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Using insight and evidence for improvement&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;· To share best practice with colleagues and peers to ensure smooth running of the team projects and work streams.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Developing an excellent organisation&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;· To ensure health, safety and wellbeing of all staff within the department.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;· To ensure compliance with all confidentiality and governance requirements within the department.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;· To support the organisation’s ways of working, model its values and champion the NHS Constitution.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;· To support NHS England &amp; NHS Improvement in the delivery of the 5 Year Forward View maintaining a clear understanding of the values and behaviours of the organisation.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;· To be part of an embedded culture of efficiency, effectiveness, productivity and sustainability.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Key Functional Responsibilities&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Project Management&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;· Undertake information/project analysis.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;· Participate in relevant internal and external working groups/projects to provide information/analyst advice and support and to maintain data collection systems for its effective use by the team.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;· Analyse and report on data and monitor the processing of data and information.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;NHS England and NHS Improvement East of England have three bases within the region located at :&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Victoria House, Capital Park, Fulbourn, Cambridge CB21 5XA&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Swift House, Hedgerows Business Park, Colchester Road, Chelmsford CM2 5PF&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Charter House, Parkway, Welwyn Garden City, Hertfordshire AL8 6JL&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Please note that the position is office based but currently based at home due to the pandemic. Contract: fixed term up to 12 months&lt;/p&gt;
